headline: Former Security Lead for Tesla’s Gigafactory Network Joins The Nuclear Company
summary: WASHINGTON, September 22, 2025--The Nuclear Company, which is leading gigawatt-scale deployment of nuclear power across America and pioneering the modernization of nuclear construction, today announced the hiring of Mike Marty as Vice President, Security. A decorated U.S. Marine Corps veteran and global security leader, Marty brings more than two decades of experience protecting some of the most complex operations in the world, including Tesla’s sprawling Gigafactory network.

headline: US High Growth Tech Stocks to Watch for Potential Expansion
summary: As the United States stock market continues to reach new heights, with major indices like the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite posting consecutive weeks of gains, investors are paying close attention to high-growth sectors such as technology. In this dynamic environment, identifying tech stocks with strong potential for expansion involves considering factors like innovative product offerings and strategic partnerships that align well with current market trends.

headline: Palantir Technologies (PLTR) Is Up 6.5% After Securing £750M UK Defence AI Contract
summary: In the past week, the UK Ministry of Defence announced a landmark partnership with Palantir Technologies, awarding the company its largest-ever foreign contract worth £750 million (US$950 million) to expand AI-powered capabilities across the British military. This five-year agreement not only deepens Palantir’s presence in UK defense, healthcare, and public safety, but also highlights the company’s accelerating move into international markets beyond its traditional US government...
